reviewText: This film provides an insiders access to material never seen before by the public. We see photographs, home movies, tender moments, and exclusive interviews that capture the life and times of this Hollywood legend. Everyone who loves film should have this one in their collection.
Short video review for Jack L. Warner : The Last Mogul documentary. Two thumbs up from me! --Jeremy

For the student of film history, or the newcomer to the world of early Hollywood, this engrossing portrait provides plenty of memorable material.  The filmmaker is the grandson of the movie's subject, and the honor of profiling the man is well-balanced with an editorial eye.  The archival material is great, and this is well worth seeing.
